'''''L'chayim''''' ('''{{hbrlamed}}{{hbrsheva}}{{hbrhet}}{{hbrpatah}}{{hbryyod}}{{hbrhiriqm}}{{hbrmems}}''' '''{{unicode|LəḤayyîm}}''', literally, "to [[life]]") is a [[Hebrew language|Hebrew]] [[toast (honor)|toast]] and an expression of goodwill. In [[United States|American]] [[popular culture]], the phrase was granted a wide audience through the [[song]] "L'chayim" in the [[musical theater|musical]] ''[[Fiddler on the Roof]]''.

